<section containing-doc="D.C. Code" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library">
  <num>19-604.08</num>
  <heading>Capacity of transferor.</heading>
  <text>The capacity required to make or revoke a transfer on death deed is the same as the capacity required to make a will.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 19-230" type="History">Mar. 19, 2013, D.C. Law 19-230, § 2(b), 59 DCR 13606</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>